                     <interp inst="t18310512-141-person1054" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. I took the prisoner with the boots in his hand, walking with them - it was between half-past six and seven o'clock; I saw the witness walking some distance behind, without a hat, and I stopped the prisoner, as I suspected he had stolen them.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. These boots were on the pavement, between two shop-fronts - I took them up, and walked nearly a mile; I never offered to run.</p>
